  "chunk_index": 44,
  "summary": "Following a conversation with Kaname regarding the symbolic nature of women's presence in certain families, Kou decides to take decisive action regarding Yuzu. Driven by a premonition, Kou visits Yuzu's room and finds her wearing a black dress. Adopting a harsh and determined attitude intended to prevent a potential tragedy, he insists that she leave the city of Kurage with him.\n\nKou drives Yuzu in a Piazza car to Arashiyama, where they walk along the south bank of the Arashiyama Gorge near the Katsura River amidst a cold, desolate landscape. After two hours, they visit a coffee shop in Sita. During their meeting, Kou confronts Yuzu about her grief and her connection to the Miura family. He challenges her claim that she is mourning Shizuma, arguing that because she lacks a blood relation to the family, her sadness is actually a form of self-pity and an attempt to escape reality.\n\nKou accuses Yuzu of using Shizuma as a puppet to facilitate her own escape from fate, asserting that while Shizuma resisted fate, Yuzu is merely attempting to flee from it. As Yuzu enters a state of hysteria and her logic collapses, Kou slams his hands on the table to suppress her emotional outburst, drawing the attention of other customers in the shop.",
